### 1. CSS Styles

For the purpose of this response, I'll make assumptions on font sizes and provide similar fonts using Google Fonts.

```css
/* styles.css */

body {
    font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; /* You can replace this with a similar Google font if needed */
    background-color: #f7f7f7;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

.container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
}

.header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 50px;
}

.header .brand {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: bold;
}

.header .nav {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
}

.nav a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: black;
}

.product-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: 30px;
    margin-bottom: 50px;
}

.product {
    background-color: #ffffff;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 20px;
}

.product img {
    width: 100%;
    object-fit: contain;
}

.product-name {
    font-size: 16px;
    margin-top: 10px;
}

.product-color {
    color: grey;
    font-size: 14px;
}

.product-price {
    font-size: 16px;
    margin-top: 5px;
}

.footer {
    display: flex;
    gap: 30px;
}

.footer img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
}
```

### 2. React Component Structure (simplified)

Here is a basic structure using Next.js and React:

```javascript
// pages/index.js

import React from 'react';
import '../styles.css';

const products = [
    { name: "CLOVELLY HAND TOWEL", color: "Clay", price: "$49 NZD" },
    // ... Add other products similarly
];

const HomePage = () => {
    return (
        <div className="container">
            <div className="header">
                <div className="brand">BAINA</div>
                <div className="nav">
                    <a href="#">SHOP</a>
                    <a href="#">THOUGHTFUL GIFTING</a>
                    <a href="#">ABOUT</a>
                    <a href="#">COMMUNITY</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div className="product-grid">
                {products.map(product => (
                    <div className="product" key={product.name}>
                        <img src="/path_to_image.jpg" alt={product.name} /> {/* Replace with appropriate image path */}
                        <div className="product-name">{product.name}</div>
                        <div className="product-color">{product.color}</div>
                        <div className="product-price">{product.price}</div>
                    </div>
                ))}
            </div>

            {/* Add footer content similarly */}
        </div>
    );
};

export default HomePage;
```

Please note:

- You'd need to have Next.js set up with a CSS loader to import and use CSS. If you're using Next.js version 9.3 and up, you can use the built-in CSS support.
- Product images paths need to be updated appropriately.
- The CSS and React code provided are basic and might need adjustments to match the exact design and responsiveness of the website from the image.

